args: You are here for Zardin's beauty course,\nyes? Join the line, please.
That is already twenty people; shall I\ntell any new arrivals that you're booked\nfor the day?
Never! I shant turn away any who\nseek my help.
Bringing out their beauty will only\nmagnify my own, after all.
Very well. But do try to take some time\nto rest. Beauty sleep, and all that.
Pish posh. My beauty is resilient.\nNow, I must get back to work!
He hasn't stopped in days.\nIt's bound to catch up with him.
I hope he knows what he's doing...
We are in your room; welcome back.
My room? But what about my patrons?!
We explained the situation and\nasked they return home. You are\nno help to anyone unconscious.
You should thank Cleo. She's been\nwatchin' over ya this whole time.
Ya know, fer a guy who loves his mirror,\nya really shoulda seen this comin'.
Yer makeup might be the best around,\nbut it can't hide yer exhaustion.
Psh. As if I, the avatar of perfection,\ncould ever fall victim to such things.
I suppose looking pale as a corpse\nis the latest trend?
...You're right. Looking closer, I see I've\ngrown weak.
I still look beautiful, mind you—but I\nappreciate your concern.
Will you take some time off now?
I have a question for you, Zardin.
What makes you so devoted to it,\nat the expense of everything else?
I told you about my past once before,\ndid I not?
My stunning visage is a gift from\nmy mother, and in realizing that I\nregained the will to live.

Seeing my mother's face in my own
makes me feel as if our memories
together live on, and that beauty
gives me strength.
For that reason, I strive to become\nmore and more beautiful.
Since starting work as a beautician,\nhowever, my thoughts have shifted\nslightly.

Staring at my own beauty is no longer
my sole source of pleasure; the act of
becoming more beautiful is enjoyable
as well.
My potential lies in my beauty,\nand ultimately it is my very\nreason for living.
Well, that certainly explains your devotion.
If it's yer whole reason for living,\nthere's no point in workin' so\nhard ya can't do it no more!
Ranzal is right.\nYou need to pace yourself.
Take your rest, and come back stronger;\nthen you can show us all that potential\nyou speak of.
Heh. All right. I shall take my time\nand recover fully.
Even in light of this failure, I can feel\nmyself growing more beautiful.
Once I'm back in peak condition,\nI imagine my beauty will follow suit.
The only way to know for sure is to rest.
A few days should be plenty.
Yes, yes, very well. For the sake of my\nlong-term beauty, I shall heed your advice.
Once I am recovered, you shall witness\na beauty the world has yet to behold!
That shall be my gift to you for your aid\nin this troubling time.
